x4freetext: Measurements were performed at the
University of Notre Dame`s Nuclear Science Laboratory
using 10-MV Tandem Pelletron accelerator
Self-supporting carbon targets were used, ranging in
thickness from 11 to 25 mu-g/cm2. For yield
normalization purposes, a thin layer of gold, between
0.2 and 2 mu-g/cm2 thick, was evaporated onto each of
the carbon targets.
Thirty-two silicon detectors were placed
approximately 63 cm from the target in approximately
5deg increments, sampling angles from 24.0deg to
169.5deg. Two sets of collimators limited the angular
coverage of each detector. In this way, for a given
energy, all 32 angles were measured simultaneously
